##Quarantine Diary 20200131

Wechat. Huochaolegal

A shepherd likes to travel, but never forgets his flock.

Play Music | read better

Thank you for your attention, reading and sharing

Yesterday, just after the plane landed, the mobile phone was turned on to let the parents know that everything was okay. People began to swarm. They got up and collected their things from the luggage rack. The announcement on the plane suddenly rang, "For passengers on this flight, Mr. Huo Chao, as a confirmed case of COVID-19 has been detected on your previous flight, please proceed to the boarding gate for examination, while the rest of you remain in your seats... "

Back in Cambodia, I couldn't resist swiping the news of the epidemic on my mobile phone at almost any moment. When I first saw the official announcement of the first confirmed case in Cambodia, the whole world was in the same cool heat, and rumors were spreading, the most common surgical masks soared from $1 to $10 a pack, and under all kinds of false and true information, went to a better local hospital in Sihanoukville the next day to register, but saw the backward medical conditions there, the findings may not be comparable to the first-tier city community hospitals in China's treatment environment, only the most basic examination. After that, as someone with a high degree of suspicion about possible contact with a confirmed infected person, do your best to protect not only yourself, but everyone you meet.

Customs and medical staff were patient enough to ask me about my temperature and health. Everything was fine, but they said it was because the big data captured by the Public Security Bureau confirmed that I had actually been on a plane with a confirmed patient, therefore, in the light of the special circumstances of the current epidemic, the need for local isolation has actually made me feel a lot better. Instead of having my own unfounded suspicion, I would rather have such a clear answer, and now that I am in the country, i still remember my family telling me to put a $5 tip in my passport when I crossed the border from Sihanouk, so customs officers wouldn't bother with my luggage.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Airport quarantine zone, January 30,2020

The rest of it, for me, was a lot of firsts. Under the friendly guidance of customs officers, they walked through an open diplomatic channel for the first time, were kindly led by medical staff to get into an ambulance in the hospital for the first time, and were carefully instructed by the quarantine staff. And went through the quarantine procedures... .

It was like being on a big screen. It was happening right in front of me.

If there is any doubt, or if there is any doubt, it is certainly there, but after all, in so many days of all-round, multi-angle, three-dimensional propaganda by the Chinese and foreign media, we understand that this epidemic will not happen overnight, it is also not easy, as an ordinary law-abiding citizens, now can do, is as much as possible a little bit of cooperation, do their part, believe that as long as through the cold tunnel, you can see the brilliant light.

On the plane back, I watched the The Cassandra Crossing, the natural disaster is never the most terrible, terrible is a man made accident, isolation on the way to the orderly, enough peace of mind.

Of course, the living conditions of the isolated accommodation are not so different from what I expected. The isolated accommodation transformed into a single room in an industrial area can guarantee a basic life, but it is only a basic life. It is certainly far from the comfortable comfort of isolation at home, yesterday arrived to clean up also tired of rest. Good thing I brought a five-terabyte hard drive before I went on this trip. With lots of undoctored photos and unwatched movies...

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Of course, as I entered the quarantine zone, I also gained a group of Internet friends who were close by but could not meet. I do not know the specific reason why each of them came in. However, it seems that everyone is also very friendly, there was even some conversation that seemed like fun...

There are a few that I have been isolated observation of the small partner, thoughtful to give me some suitable for living in the game projects, film resources and even Comfort Hongbao... Let me feel ahead of time this period of isolation life is not easy and bitter.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"3-floor Quarantine Group" , in order to protect personal privacy, chat screenshots have done part of processing

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"3-floor Quarantine Group" , in order to protect personal privacy, chat screenshots have done part of processing

I got up this morning and began to organize the photos in my camera. I saw myself walking along the beach in the sunset the night before I left Cambodia. I met a local man who was building Angkor Wat by the sea alone with sand, in the glimpses of the journey, one can also see a people who have experienced the suffering of the Khmer Rouge, and who still have hope, longing and a good pursuit for the future.

By the sea in Sihanouk port, January 29,2019

—End—
